#
#   Architecture:
#     1. Developer writes a Canvas contract — a typed
#        `*.canvas.js` module that declares typed `models` (the
#        typed SQLite schema), typed `actions` (the typed
#        action-handlers), and typed `views` (the typed read
#        queries)
#     2. `canvas run path/to/contract.canvas.js` boots the typed
#        Express HTTP API + typed network-explorer UI + opens
#        the typed libp2p host
#     3. Clients (browser, Node SDK, mobile native) submit
#        typed signed actions via the typed HTTP API or typed
#        libp2p stream
#     4. Actions are appended to the typed GossipLog +
#        materialized into the typed SQLite database via the
#        contract's typed action-handlers
#     5. The typed GossipLog gossip-propagates to peers via
#        typed libp2p Gossipsub + typed Bitswap-style typed
#        on-demand sync
